The permutation procedures described above to approximate the statistical significance for local trend analysis have several drawbacks. First, the calculated p-values have substantial inherent variability associated with the randomness in permutation unless the number of permutations is very large. Second, the procedure is computationally expensive– the computational time scales linearly with the inverse of the required p-value precision, which is prohibitive for all-versus-all pairwise analysis of high-throughput datasets.

