We choose type-I error threshold to be 0.05. For t=0, the results show good agreement. With D=0, we have 482 (62 %) and 263 (34 %) out of 780 found non-significant and significant, respectively, by both methods. In total 745 (96 %) are in agreement. Among the 33 (4 %) OTU pairs with discordant significance by P
